      interface  Define 
      Classes in com.javax0.jdsl.analyzers that implement Analyzer 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      class  AlternativesAnalyzer
      Implements an analyzer that accepts an input if one of the underlying analyzers accept the starts of the input.
      class  ListAnalyzer
      Implements an analyzer that accepts a code if the underlying analyzers accept the starts of the input one after the other.
      class  NoExecutorListAnalyzer
      This list analyzer has no executor.
      class  PassThroughAnalyzer
      PassThroughAnalyzer only invokes the underlying analyzer.
      class  SequenceAnalyzer
      Implements an analyzer that accepts a code if the underlying analyzers accept the starts of the input a few times.
      class  SkippingAnalyzer
      A skipping analyzer is an analyzer that eats up character from the start of the input but does not produce any executor.
      class  SpaceIgnoringAnalyzer
      SpaceIgnoringAnalyzer(s) are analyzers that ignore parts of the input, typically white space.
      class  WhiteSpaceSkippingAnalyzer
      Analyzer that can be used in SpaceIgnoringAnalyzers to skips white spaces.
